social_posts.post_text:
A quick reel to show y’all the first tattoo of 2023 (started in 2022) and to say I’m slowly getting back to work! 
Last year sure was something. This year has kicked off to a rough start as I’ve been dealing with a sick and jet lagged baby, but this week it seems that things are starting to settle. 
I never made an official end of the year post as I’ve been busy just surviving, but I would still love to share some highlights soon. 
I had a bunch more emails I wanted to get to from my last round of bookings, but at this point I’m thinking maybe I should just start the new year fresh and reopen for new requests. What do y’all think? If you’re still waiting and would like to snag a last minute January/February appointment, drop a comment and I’ll get back to ya 😌🤍 
.
.
.

Working hard in real life equates to neglecting my online presence - but isn’t real life what matters most anyway? 
Thank you Elijah for continuing to come to me with your cool ideas and trust - I had a lot of fun bringing this to life for you! 🤍

Happy Valentine’s Day everyone 🤍 Here’s the Venus of Willendorf I got to create for Melody yesterday. 
I hope everyone got to spend some time with loved ones today! 🥰

I’m opening my books for spring/summer bookings on March 17th! I’ve taken a lot of time to re-evaluate my booking process and how to make it more efficient so that it won’t take me literal months to finish going through emails. 
I’ll be posting some updates in my stories over the next week, including a Q&A so turn on post notifications to make sure you don’t miss out! As always, I’ll also share a countdown to when to send in your emails. 
I’m so thankful to be doing what i do- even though this industry as a whole can be a rough ride, I’m in awe every day to get to create for a living. Y’all are truly magnificent people and I love that I’ve gotten to meet so many wonderful folks through art. Love you all. Can’t wait to see y’all. 🤍

Happy international women’s day! Take some time today to celebrate the badass women in your life. ✨ here’s some tattoos I’ve done on some amazing people, a mix of fresh & healed work, and mostly a celebration of femininity 🤍 #grlpwr #internationalwomensday

EDIT - I’ve closed my books while I finish reading everyone’s requests! 

Please read these slides for a couple of updates I’ve made this round to (hopefully) streamline the process. 🤞🏻 This round of bookings is for new and repeat clients, and I’ll be booking for April-June! 
Hope to read y’all’s ideas soon! 🤍 
.
.

I’m reopening my books for the remainder of the year this Thursday! 

Booking link will be posted in my bio prior to the opening.

I’m taking on new and returning clients, open to both big or small projects, as always I love to take on a variety of both.

A little reel to commemorate just some of the amazing ideas I got bring to life in 2023. Needless to say, it was another year of incredible growth, learning moments and more… my first full year as a mom too. 
I’ve learned to appreciate so many things- and I’m looking forward to seeing what 2024 brings. As I’m getting ready for maternity leave again (yes you read that right 😅), I’ve left the booking link in my bio to fill any last minute openings as I wrap up larger continuing projects. 
I truly don’t have the words for the appreciation I have for all of you who continue to support me and allowing me to do what I do 🥹🤍 
Here’s to another year- and remember, even if “all” you did was get by and survive- that’s already amazing. Hope to see you here this year 🤍
.
